properties.otherAdvice:
AFL: Sydney Swans v Carlton Blues at the SCG. Gates open 11.25am, VFL first bounce 11.30am, AFL first bounce 3.20pm, finish around 6pm.

Traffic will be heavier than usual on roads approaching and around Moore Park as thousands of fans travel to the stadium. Motorists should allow extra travel time on the Eastern Distributor, Moore Park Rd, Cleveland St, Anzac Pde and Lang Rd. 

Driver Ave will be partially closed outside the stadium from 12.15pm and will reopen when crowds have safely cleared the area after the game.

Special event clearways will be in effect from 1pm to 7pm on sections of Moore Park Rd, Albion St, Lang Rd, Chalmers St, Fitzroy St, Flinders St and Foveaux St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

properties.headline: Tour De Cure cycle - Sunday 30 May to Tuesday 1 June - WOLLONGONG TO NORWEST VIA HUSKISSON, KIAMA AND BOWRAL Princes Highway, Bolong Road, Old Hume Highway and Old Windsor Road
properties.otherAdvice:
Around 100 cyclists will take part in the annual three-day Tour De Cure event travelling from Wollongong to Norwest via Huskisson, Bowral and Kiama from 8am on Sunday 30 May, finishing by 4:30pm on Tuesday 1 June. 

  • On Sunday 30 May: cyclists will travel from Wollongong to Huskisson via Kiama and Nowra along Woollamia Rd, Princes Hwy and Bolong Rd.
  • On Monday 31 May: cyclists will travel from Huskisson to Bowral via Kangeroo Valley along The Wool Rd, Princes Hwy, Turpentine Rd and Bryces Rd.
  • On Tuesday 1 June:  cyclists will travel from Boweral to Norwest via Luddenham along Old Hume Hwy, The Northern Rd, Sunnyholt Rd and Old Windsor Rd.

Motorists should be aware of cyclists using the Princes Hwy and to exercise caution and remember when overtaking cyclists to leave a 1.5m distance on roads with speed limits over 60km/h and a 1m distance on roads 60km/h or under.

properties.publicTransport: Some buses may experience delays and light rail services may be impacted. Check transportnsw.info service alerts for details.
properties.adviceB: Avoid the area; Use an alternative route
